The paper deals with the problem of synchronizing two sets of data, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus on the Hamming distance metric suggests a connection to coding theory (cs.DC) and error-correcting codes. The problem of reconciling similar sets of data is also relevant to similarity search (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
